19
00:01:18,020 --> 00:01:24,530
Several things need to happen like updating inventory, notifying the shipping department, and sending

20
00:01:24,530 --> 00:01:26,990
an email for confirmation to the customer.

21
00:01:27,200 --> 00:01:34,130
So all these actions can be triggered by throwing an order created domain event from the order aggregate.

22
00:01:34,250 --> 00:01:37,400
So how we can dispatch these domain events.

23
00:01:37,400 --> 00:01:41,540
How we can raise and dispatching domain events into our application.

24
00:01:41,540 --> 00:01:48,020
So when we talk about the raising the event within the order aggregate, when order new order placed

25
00:01:48,020 --> 00:01:53,990
and it adding an order created domain event to the collection of the domain event in the order aggregate.

26
00:01:54,080 --> 00:01:57,830
So the question is how to dispatching these domain events.

27
00:01:57,980 --> 00:02:04,010
So in order to dispatching this event, this will be typically done in the infrastructure layer and

28
00:02:04,010 --> 00:02:06,470
often in the repository or unit of work.

29
00:02:06,470 --> 00:02:13,190
That means after saving to do changes into database, the domain events are dispatched to their respective

30
00:02:13,190 --> 00:02:14,000
