38
00:02:41,750 --> 00:02:46,910
So why we use Entity Framework Core Save Change Interceptor for this action?

39
00:02:46,910 --> 00:02:53,450
Because it is a best practice to use these Entity Framework core Save change interceptor for dispatching

40
00:02:53,450 --> 00:02:59,810
domain events, because it allows you to hook into the lifecycle of database operations, particularly

41
00:02:59,810 --> 00:03:02,570
after changes have been successfully committed.

42
00:03:03,170 --> 00:03:09,950
So after deciding to using these save chains in Susceptor, we can go to the steps when implementing

43
00:03:09,950 --> 00:03:11,360
dispatching domain events.

44
00:03:11,390 --> 00:03:14,840
The first step is create a save change interceptor class.

45
00:03:14,840 --> 00:03:20,660
We will implement a class that inherits from the save change interceptor and override methods like saving

46
00:03:20,660 --> 00:03:22,730
changes or saving change async.

47
00:03:22,730 --> 00:03:26,270
And the second step is identify and dispatch domain events.

48
00:03:26,270 --> 00:03:32,600
In the override methods, we can check the Dbcontext for entities that have unprocessed domain events,

49
00:03:32,600 --> 00:03:36,980
and after that we will dispatch these events using a mechanism like mediator.

50
00:03:36,980 --> 00:03:41,000
That means we will use mediator library when dispatching these domain events.

51
00:03:41,270 --> 00:03:48,800
And after that you can see we will use Domain Event Dispatcher interceptor class to perform these operations

52
00:03:48,800 --> 00:03:51,410
and inherit from the save change interceptor.

53
00:03:51,410 --> 00:03:54,500
And lastly we will register the interceptor.

54
00:03:54,500 --> 00:03:59,630
In this step we will register the interceptor in the Dependency Injection class of our infrastructure

55
00:03:59,630 --> 00:04:00,170
layer.

56
00:04:00,290 --> 00:04:06,380
So dispatching domain events using the Entity Framework core Save Change Interceptor is a powerful approach

57
00:04:06,380 --> 00:04:10,400
to handling business operations that are triggered by the changes in the domain.

